'''AlKhidmat (اﻟﺧدﻣﺖ) Foundation''' is network that provides humanitarian services across [[Pakistan]]. It is registered with the Government of Pakistan as a [[non-governmental organisation]] (NGO) under the Societies Act XXI of 1860.<ref name="AKhistory">{{cite web|url=http://al-khidmatfoundation.org/history.php |title=Al-Khidmat Foundation Pakistan: History |accessdate=14 May 2011 |publisher=Al-Khidmat Foundation |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110724231843/http://al-khidmatfoundation.org/history.php |archivedate=24 July 2011 }}</ref> {{As of|2018|January}}, its president was Muhammad Abdul Shakoor.<ref name="AKabout">{{cite web|url=http://al-khidmatfoundation.org/aboutus.php |title=Al-Khidmat Foundation Pakistan: About Us |accessdate=14 May 2011 |publisher=Al-Khidmat Foundation |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110724025605/http://al-khidmatfoundation.org/aboutus.php |archivedate=24 July 2011 }}</ref> Its sole aim is service to humanity without discrimination of religion, race, cast, sect, language, or political affiliation.<ref name="AKhome">{{cite web|url=http://al-khidmatfoundation.org/index.php |title=Al-Khidmat Foundation Pakistan |accessdate=14 May 2011 |publisher=Al-Khidmat Foundation |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110623202215/http://al-khidmatfoundation.org/index.php |archivedate=23 June 2011 }}</ref> Mainly, Alkhidmat Foundation works in seven (7) key areas such as: Disaster Management, Education, Health Services, Clean Water, Orphan Care, Mawakhat and Community Services which altogether cover all fields of the life<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://alkhidmat.org/president-message/|title=President Message – ALKHIDMAT FOUNDATION PAKISTAN|website=alkhidmat.org|access-date=2018-11-27}}</ref>. Alkhidmat Foundation has expanded its operations to other countries as well and the organization is engaged in welfare activities in Bangladesh, Syria, Indonesia, Malaysia Nepal and [https://alkhidmat.org/ Myanmar].

Alkhidmat Foundation Pakistan is one of the advancing, non-for-profit and autonomous organization, wholly devoted to humanitarian cause. In spite of the fact that AlKhidmat Foundation authoritatively enrolled in 1990 as an NGO, its relief and humanitarian records goes back to the times of Independence of Pakistan with initially focusing on furnishing safe house, nourishing and treating outcasts and protecting the deserves which has later become the trade mark of Alkhidmat Foundation Pakistan.

The Foundation has presence all over Pakistan including all the provinces and federally administered areas. It has one of the quick and vast grass-root structure which is vigilant to sudden emergency situation all time.

One of the latest initiative of Alkhidmat Foundation is its Orphan Care Program where the Foundation is having two fold activities i.e. 'Aghosh Homes' and 'Orphan Family Support'. These two programs are for those orphans who are below the age of 14 where the Foundation provides complete support to the child and his family. The Orphan homes of the Foundation are one of the best where state of the art facilities are provided to the children. This program is sponsored by many individuals and international donors<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://alkhidmat.org/orphan-care-program/#Aghosh-Homes|title=Orphan Care Program – ALKHIDMAT FOUNDATION PAKISTAN|website=alkhidmat.org|access-date=2018-11-28}}</ref>. 

Alongside other NGOs, the Al-Khidmat Foundation participated in relief operations for the victims of the [[2005 Kashmir earthquake|2005 earthquake]]. Al-Khidmat is reported to have provided over 10,000 shelters and makeshift homes for those affected.<ref>[http://www.geo.tv/quake/english-31-12-05.asp "Relief operations continue in quake zone"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080524013332/http://www.geo.tv/quake/english-31-12-05.asp |date=24 May 2008 }}. The News International, Pakistan, 31 December 2005. Retrieved 14 May 2011.</ref>
[[File:Relief1.png|thumb|Right|280px| Trucks with relief goods heading for areas affected by floods]]

In the wake of 2010 floods in Pakistan, the Japanese Government provided financial support to the Al-Khidmat Foundation to support the people of [[Charsadda]] who were affected by the flood.<ref>[http://www.reliefweb.int/rw/rwb.nsf/db900SID/MCOI-89GCW5?OpenDocumentl "Pakistan: The Government of Japan grants US$ 407,318 (Rs. 33.95 million approx.) for the project for Supporting the Flood Affected People in Charsadda, Khyber Pakhtunkhwa"]. Reliefweb, Islamabad, 17 September 2010. Retrieved 14 May 2011.</ref>

