In [[Hinduism]], '''Dhatri''' ([[Sanskrit]] - ''earth'') mother earth, a name for [[Parvati]] in Lalita sahasranaama. It is also one of the names of the [[solar deity]], one of the [[Aditya]]s.<ref>{{cite book|title=Original Sanskrit Texts on the Origin and History of the People of India, Their Religion and Institutions, Volume 2 |page=106|author=John Muir}}</ref>  He is also a god of health and domestic tranquility. He can be called (at least in spirit) in [[tantra]] or magic by drawing tantras and chanting [[Historical Vedic religion|Vedic]] [[hymn]]s. Often invoked during major [[yagna]]s such as [[Ashwamedha]] yagna.

